    • Method Detail

      • process

        boolean process(ContentEvent event)
        Entry point for the Processor code. This method is called once for every event received.
        Parameters:
        event - the event to be processed.
        Returns:
        true if successful, false otherwise.

      • onCreate

        void onCreate(int id)
        Initializes the Processor. This method is called once after the topology is set up and before any call to the process method.
        Parameters:
        id - the identifier of the processor.

      • newProcessor

        Processor newProcessor(Processor processor)
        Creates a copy of a processor. This method is used to instantiate multiple instances of the same Processsor .
        Parameters:
        processor - the processor to be copied.
        Returns:
        a new instance of the Processor.
